<br>
No amount of killing anything else is comparable.<br>
<br>
If you see someone killing Tormax, hang around, but stay out of the way.  That's a big one. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/uxorshaik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xorshaik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 460<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(5/14/02 6:55:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=770.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Getting CoV/Coldain faction</span><hr size=1> Killing in general in the Tormax area seems to be the most efficient +CoV faction.<br>
<br>
My findings after a Klandicar kill (took me from max ally to kindly) were:<br>
<br>
After 30 GD giant for hits and 50 hits from a 10th ring war (didn't stay to the end, had to sleep), I was still kindly.<br>
<br>
26 faction hits in Tormax area (less than one hour) took me from kindly (high kindly, most likely) to max ally.<br>
<br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
An evening in WToV did the following:<br>
Telk: Max ally =&gt; Kindly<br>
Gozz: Kindly =&gt; Amiable<br>
<br>
2 WW kills took me to Indifferent.<br>
<br>
Since then, I've been in on a Vindi kill (including around 20-30 other arena kills) and I am at amiable. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/usenseixanathos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sensei Xanathos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(5/30/02 5:19:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=770.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Getting CoV/Coldain faction</span><hr size=1> Follow your server uber guild in arena, punch Vindi, then punch Tormax, then punch Statue of RZ, then punch AoW = ally to CoV in 1 hour (assuming they win!)<br>
<br>
Don't forget to FD after you punch, don't mess their fights! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/udarury.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Darury</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 167<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(6/6/02 6:37:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=770.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Getting CoV/Coldain faction</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Do the giant toes/helms give any -giant factions? gonna try to get both ally dragon and giant and thinking that this may be the way to do it. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
It's impossible to have both CoV and Giant faction.  <br>
<br>
You can have Ally Kromriff/Kromzek/Tormax (giant factions) and Coldain.  Brief explanation:<br>
<br>
Kill dwarves until you are max ally to giants.  Do NOT turn in heads or kobold paws yet.  You'll max out bad Coldain faction long before you max ally giants.<br>
<br>
Once there, begin killing giants to get +Coldain.  Do this until you are apprehensive or dubious with giants.  Now begin turning in your heads and kobold paws to Captain Bvellos. Do not use the Recruiter as he will give -Coldain.<br>
<br>
You may need to purchase heads after you begin repairing your Coldain faction. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujoker9950.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Joker9950</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(6/18/02 7:00:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=770.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Getting CoV/Coldain faction</span><hr size=1> if u punch the AoW and die do u still get the faction hits?<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usenseixanathos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sensei Xanathos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(6/19/02 11:59:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=770.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Getting CoV/Coldain faction</span><hr size=1> You must be alive when mob dies to get the faction hit: if you're gonna give a punch to AoW, let the guild fight him for a while before you hit, fight lasts long enough, you have plenty of time, don't risk.<br>
If they are going to lose, /q out immediately. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubodikibadachi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BodiKibadachi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 2431<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(6/20/02 3:26:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=770.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://kibadachi.homestead.com/files/groohead.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Getting CoV/Coldain faction</span><hr size=1> I was Max Ally until I survived a Klandicar killing an took a massive faction hit. Then a Wyvern attacked the Cleric in our party and I helped kill him, taking another CoV hit.<br>
<br>
I ended up at Warmly.<br>
<br>
I then spent nearlt 2 hrs at the Giant fort teamed with a 60th Rogue slaughtering hte Gianst there. We killed upwards of 40+ faction mobs.<br>
<br>
I need my faction as I still dont have my BoB and want Ally, and also after Kland, we took Zland, and I got the talisman to make the Shroud of Da Brood.<br>
<br>
Harla Dar is up, and so I ran over, checked faction, still Warmly. Managed to get the speech (after some spamming) and held my breath and handed the talisman in. Got my shroud, and better still, the faction I got took me all the way back to Ally again.<br>
<br>
Off course, I bolloxed it up again by surving another Kland fight, but thats another story.... <p><p align="center"><FONT FACE="Tempus Sans ITC"><img src="http://bodi.morgyn.org/ban.jpg"><br><a href="http://bodi.morgyn.org/">Bodi Kibadachi</a>, Master of the Celestial Fists on Bristlebane</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=gater>Gater</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(6/20/02 5:08:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=770.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Getting CoV/Coldain faction</span><hr size=1> Do you still get the faction hit if you FD after you hit one of these mobs? I thought that wiped memory/aggro/exp... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzuminozufeilon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zumino Zufeilon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(6/20/02 5:47:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=770.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Getting CoV/Coldain faction</span><hr size=1> Been Said before, I'll say it again<br>
<br>
DO NOT TAG MOBS IN THE 10TH RING WAR<br>
<br>
sorry for the shouting.<br>
<br>
If you're 55-60, and you know who's running the war(or know some people in it) feel free to ask, but trust me, that is one of the fastest ways to royally screw up one of the more annoying quest fights in the game, same thing goes for the 8th shawl fights.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Also, for the person who asked, Kael faction can be gotten by<br>
<br>
1) Killing dragons(or mobs in SS) in Velious(this actually, only gets you +Kromzek faction, and you'll have to do heads/Paws to get tormax/Rif)<br>
<br>
2) Killing Dorfs in Velious(this get's you +zek/Rif, and heads to turn in for Tormax, but has the downside of making you KoS in Thrug, a city that I find to be very convient location/tradeskill-wise)<br>
<br>
3) Velk/Yeli/Dain, Vindi/Dain give you a nice Tormax faction hit, but Velk is pretty slim.  And you'll still need to work on Rif/Zek.<br>
<br>
<br>
Myself, I did it the long way, I killed in WW/SS till I was warmly to Kromzek, then turned in paws/dorf heads(that I bought to avoid the -Coldain hit) until I was Ally to Tormax/Zek, an non-kos to rif(who cares bout the frosties anyways), if your willing to kill coldain faction, you'll have a much faster time of it then I did. <p><BR>
