<br>
Do you need Yeli faction for Bracer of Benevolence? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cerberusc>Cerberusc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/15/02 5:35:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=770.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Getting CoV/Coldain faction</span><hr size=1> I found a nice easy way to get CoV faction the other day. In Eastern Wastes, there is a camp that contains giant prison guards, a couple orcs, and 3 ogre mercenaries. The ogre mercenaries are your primary target. They con dark blue to 51, and light blue to 52, so they're in the high 30's. Everytime you kill one of them, you get -to giants and + to CoV. Also, the ogres drop &quot;Mercenary Assignments&quot; or something along the line of that. They're magic and no drop. Get as many of these as you can. After you've killed the 3 ogres, you can wander around and kill the prison guards (Toes and giant helms) or ulthork (dont have to do with CoV faction, but turning in tusks to otter in CS can get you a high end gem). Take allll of those mercenary assignments to Sentry Kcor in skyshrine for a faction adjustment. Hurts giants, gives + to CoV and yelinak. I was able to get my friends char from dubious to amiable to CoV in about 2 hours, no problem. Hope this helps!<br>
